RARELY
DIAGNOSED
PREOPERATIVELY
IS
AN
UNCOMMON
DISEASE
ACCOUNTING
FOR
21
OF
ALL
PEDIATRIC
ABDOMINAL
EMERGENCIES
IT
IS
OFTEN
ASSOCIATED
WITH
URINARY
OR
HEPATIC
PATHOLOGY
THE
FORMER
THE
SOURCE
OF
THE
INFECTING
ORGANISM
IN
THE
MAJORITY
OF
CASES
AND
PRESENTS
WITH
CHARACTERISTIC
SYMPTOMS
DEPENDING
UPON
WHETHER
IT
OCCURS
IN
INFANCY
OR
CHILDHOOD
THE
SYMPTOMS
AND
SIGNS
WHICH
ALLOW
FOR
A
